This is the changelog of all versions of this patch

a1.04
  -Fixed CreateDXGIFactory1

a1.12
  -Fixed SwapChain + RTVBuffer (kind of)

a1.18
  -Fixed C5 error in d3d11. Now rendering works with some D3D12 samples. For some of them, the image isn't being drawn into the created window, but the program does actually run

b1.0
  -Remade how the SwapChain works, and this is the first version where I got something rendering correctly with DirectX12 on Windows 7!

b1.02
  -Increased the wrapper compatibility. The AMD DirectX12 (https://github.com/GPUOpen-LibrariesAndSDKs/HelloD3D12) demo now works!
  -Translated the notes and log from French to English

b1.04
  -Added partial support of CreateDXGIFactory2. Some Win32 samples using CreateDXGIFactory2 are now supported

b1.07
  -Increased compatibility with other samples
  -Fixed some other errors with a microsoft sample even if it doesn't make this sample work. Basically Microsoft samples are very complex for no reason and are a pain to fix

b1.08
  -Fixed resizing a window make it crash

b1.13
  -Increased app compatibility. For example I got UnrealEngine 4 SunTemple benchmark running with D3D12 mode on Windows 7
  -Optimized a tiny bit the wrapper by removing useless logs

b1.16
  -Added config file (FPS Display [only for testings] and OutputLogFile [useful if you don't have x64dbg installed])
  -Optimized a tiny more the wrapper by caching values instead of re-calculating them
  -Added MSVC support thanks to OwnedByWuggy

b1.23
  -Reduced Cyberpunk (v1.6) crashing by quite a lot with lower settings. It might still crash on launch, just retry a second time.

b1.23.1
  -Added file description

b1.27
  -Remade the FPS counter, there are the changes:
    -Better optimization
    -Fixed overlay flickering
    -Added FPSOverlayRefreshCooldown

b1.29
  -Renamed the wrapper from dxgw to dxgi for ease to use
  -Fixed multithreading bug in CreateDXGIFactory(x)

b1.30
  -Fixed a bug that caused the NO_INTERFACE bug. This fixes Control with DirectX12

b1.32
  -Added an option to spoof the VRAM amount

b1.34
  -Fixed VSync not working with an option in the INI config file (set VSync mode to 1)
  -Fixed minimizing the program make it crash
  -Fixed VRAM detection and disabled the VRAM spoof by default (default value is 0)

b1.35
  -Fixed a bug where the program would crash if it called GetParent(IDXGIFactory) after the SwapChain creation. This fixes Grid 2019 (in DX12 mode)
